12/12/2010
ZAGREB, Croatia -- Parliament decided on Friday (December 10th) to send 30 more soldiers to Afghanistan, thus boosting the Croatian contingent in the country in the next two years to up to 350 troops. Croatian military officers are in charge of training local security forces. Croatia has been part of the International Security Assistance Force (ISAF) in Afghanistan since 2003. (Hina, Nova TV, AFP - 10/12/10)
